Backend Responsibilities (Python)

Python backend must handle all business logic and AWS operations.

1. AWS Findings Collection
Fetch organization-wide findings from delegated account.

A. AWS Inspector
Fetch:
- Findings per account
- Severity
- Resource type
- Region
- Status
- CVEs
- Vulnerability details
- Fix availability
- Aging
- Asset information

B. CSPM Findings
Fetch Security Hub findings for:
- CIS AWS Foundations Benchmark v5.0.0
- NIST Special Publication 800-53 Revision 5

Collect:
- Passed controls
- Failed controls
- Compliance percentage
- Benchmark details
- Service-level failures
- Risk posture

2. S3 Findings Count Processing
A bucket contains findings count data.

Requirements:
- Read historical findings count data.
- Process trends.
- Generate visually attractive graphs.
- Create chart exports for email attachments.
- Build trend comparison.
- Historical posture movement.

3. Owner Consolidation Logic
Important:
One owner may own multiple AWS accounts.

Requirements:
- Consolidate emails.
- Send only one email per owner.
- Include all owned accounts in one mail.
- Avoid duplicate communication.
- Support editable owner mapping.
- Support bulk owner imports.
- Handle missing owners gracefully.

